<FeaturePage
  title="No Cloud. No Telemetry. Your Machine."
  tagline="Local-First"
  description="ostk is a single Rust binary that runs on your machine. No cloud dependency, no data leaving your network. Works with local models or API models — your choice."
  relatedPages={[
    { title: "Context Injection", description: "+34.3pp improvement, even on local models", href: "/features/context-injection" },
    { title: "Model Switching", description: "Switch between local and API models mid-session", href: "/features/model-switching" },
    { title: "Secret Management", description: "API keys never enter LLM context", href: "/features/secret-management" },
  ]}
>
  <h2>What local-first means</h2>
  <p>ostk has no cloud component. The binary runs locally. State lives in <code>.ostk/</code> inside your repository. There is no account, no sign-up, no telemetry, no phone-home.</p>
  <p>Your code stays on your machine. The audit trail stays on your machine. The only network calls are the ones your agents make to LLM APIs — and even those are optional if you run local models.</p>

  <h2>Local models work</h2>
  <p>With context injection, open-weight models running locally match or beat frontier API models running without context.</p>

  <div class="data-table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Setup</th><th>Model</th><th>Resolve Rate</th><th>API Cost</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Local + context</td><td>Devstral 24B</td><td class="num">75.0%</td><td class="num">$0</td></tr>
        <tr><td>API, no context</td><td>GPT-4.1</td><td class="num">50.0%</td><td class="num">$2/MTok</td></tr>
        <tr><td>API, no context</td><td>Claude Sonnet 4</td><td class="num">65.6%</td><td class="num">$3/MTok</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <p>Devstral 24B runs on a machine with 16GB VRAM. With ostk providing context injection, it outperforms GPT-4.1 running without context — and the model runs entirely on your hardware.</p>

  <h2>How to run locally</h2>
  <pre><code># Install ostk
curl -fsSL https://ostk.ai/install | sh

# Set up a local model (e.g., via Ollama)
ollama pull devstral

# Configure your HUMANFILE to use the local model
# MODEL devstral
# AVAILABLE devstral, claude-sonnet-4

# Init and boot
ostk init
ostk boot</code></pre>

  <p>The OS works the same whether your model is local or remote. Context injection, audit trails, conflict resolution — all run locally regardless of where the LLM is.</p>

  <h2>Privacy by architecture</h2>
  <p>ostk collects nothing. The website uses <a href="https://plausible.io">Plausible</a> (privacy-first, cookie-free analytics). The binary has no analytics, no crash reporting, no usage tracking. There is no server to send data to.</p>
  <p>The <a href="/legal/privacy">privacy policy</a> is short because there is nothing to disclose.</p>
</FeaturePage>

